      <div class="lesson-bubble">
        <h1>üîê Strong Passwords</h1>

        <p><strong>What is a password?</strong><br>
        A password is a secret code that protects your accounts. Only you should know it. Think of it like the key to your house ‚Äì you wouldn't want anyone else to have a copy!</p>

        <h2>Why Strong Passwords Matter</h2>
        <p>Weak passwords are easy for hackers to guess. They have programs that can try millions of password combinations in seconds. Strong passwords keep your stuff safe by making it nearly impossible to crack.</p>

        <h2>How to Make a Strong Password</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Use 12+ characters</strong> ‚Äì Longer is stronger!</li>
          <li><strong>Mix letters, numbers, and symbols</strong> ‚Äì Like #, @, $, !</li>
          <li><strong>Avoid personal info</strong> ‚Äì No birthdays, pet names, or favorite teams</li>
          <li><strong>Never reuse passwords</strong> ‚Äì Each account should have its own unique password</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Examples</h2>
        <p><strong>Weak passwords:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li><code>monkey123</code> ‚Äì Too simple and predictable</li>
          <li><code>password</code> ‚Äì The most common (and worst!) password</li>
          <li><code>123456</code> ‚Äì Hackers try this first</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>Strong passwords:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li><code>BlueSky!Tree92$</code> ‚Äì Long, random, mixed characters</li>
          <li><code>Sunset#Wave204*</code> ‚Äì Hard to guess, easy to remember</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Pro Tip</h2>
        <p>Use a password manager if you can ‚Äì it creates and remembers super strong passwords for you!</p>

        <div class="challenge-box">
          <h3>üêµ Monkey Challenge</h3>
          <p>Imagine someone is trying to guess your password. What part of your life would they guess first? Your favorite color? Your pet's name? Your birthday?</p>
          <p><em>If your real password includes any of those things... it's time to change it!</em></p>
          
          <h4 style="margin-top: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px; color: #d97706;">Quick Quiz:</h4>
          <p style="font-style: normal; font-weight: 600; color: #333;">Which password is strongest?</p>
          
          <div class="quiz-option" onclick="checkAnswer(this, false)">
            A) <code>ilovepizza</code>
          </div>
          <div class="quiz-option" onclick="checkAnswer(this, false)">
            B) <code>MyDog2020</code>
          </div>
          <div class="quiz-option" onclick="checkAnswer(this, true)">
            C) <code>Tr33!House#92</code>
          </div>
          <div class="quiz-option" onclick="checkAnswer(this, false)">
            D) <code>password123</code>
          </div>

          <div id="quiz-feedback" class="quiz-feedback"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="complete-checkbox">
          <input type="checkbox" id="lesson-complete" onchange="markComplete()">
          <label for="lesson-complete">‚úÖ I've completed this lesson!</label>
        </div>

        <a href="lesson2.html" class="btn">Next Lesson: Spotting Scams ‚Üí</a>
